Box Model

In an HTML page, every element is displayed in box. 
Box Model:
				Margin
				Border
				Padding
				Content
In this way, every box consists of these tags around four sides.

margin: to give space outside the box, basically to seperate from the other elements.
padding: to give the space inside the box itself. By defaulty,when given padding it takes extra space outside the box.
But to get padding inside the box, we need to use:

*{											// * to add all the page
box-sizing: border-box;
}

border : to create the borders around the box. 
border : 2px black solid;   dotted dashed









Different ways to give margin, border, and padding

padding-left: 10px;
padding-right: 10px;
padding-top: 10px;
padding-bottom: 10px;

 to add specifically.

 Other Way is to :

 padding: 10px 20px 30px 15px;
 padding: top right bottom left;

 padding: 10px 20px;
 padding: top&bottom left&right;

 padding: 10px 15px 20px;
 padding:  top left&bottom right;

 All these can be replaced with margin and border also.